The paper discusses clustering on graphs with multiple edge types, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with similarity metrics between objects, which can be represented as a network. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the challenges of clustering in this context and proposes solutions. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper deals with the algorithmic challenges of clustering on multi-edged graphs. cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are less likely categories, but still possible as the paper discusses case studies based on papers on Arxiv and CIA World Factbook, which involve information retrieval and software development.
